<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>About Me | Sait Elmas</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <%- include('partials/navbar') %>

    <main style="max-width: 1000px; margin: 3rem auto; padding: 0 1rem;">
        
        <!-- Hero Section -->
        <section style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 4rem;">
            <h1 style="font-size: 3rem; color: #0f172a; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Mathematician. Engineer. Educator.</h1>
            <p style="font-size: 1.25rem; color: #475569; max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto; line-height: 1.6;">
                Bridging the gap between pure mathematics, computer science, and real-world engineering to guide the next generation of analytical minds.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Grid Layout -->
        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 3rem;">
            
            <!-- Left Column: Academic Journey -->
            <div>
                <h2 style="color: #3b82f6; border-bottom: 2px solid #cbd5e1; padding-bottom: 0.5rem;">My Academic Journey</h2>
                <p style="color: #334155; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 1.05rem;">
                    My path to education is built on a foundation of rigorous engineering and pure science. After earning my degree in Shipbuilding Engineering from <strong>Istanbul Technical University (ITU)</strong> and practicing in the field until 2016, I pursued my passion for fundamental sciences.
                </p>
                <p style="color: #334155; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 1.05rem;">
                    This drive led me to <strong>Middle East Technical University (METU)</strong>, where I completed a double major in <strong>Mathematics</strong> and <strong>Computer Engineering</strong>. I am currently continuing my academic journey there as a <strong>Ph.D.</strong> student in <strong>Mathematics</strong>. I bring this multifaceted engineering and theoretical perspective into every lesson I teach.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Right Column: Beyond the Desk -->
            <div>
                <h2 style="color: #10b981; border-bottom: 2px solid #cbd5e1; padding-bottom: 0.5rem;">Beyond the Desk</h2>
                <p style="color: #334155; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 1.05rem;">
                    Currently based in Ankara, Türkiye, I believe that a sharp mind requires a balanced life. When I am not tutoring or coding in Python and Java, I immerse myself in the world of social Latin dances, practicing Kizomba and Bachata regularly. 
                </p>
                <p style="color: #334155; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 1.05rem;">
                    I am also an avid reader of philosophy, particularly Stoicism, and hold a deep fascination for ancient history. Whether I am capturing moments through photography or exploring new ideas, I approach life with the same curiosity I bring to mathematics.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

    </main>

    <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>